  "title": "Intermediate Grammar",
  "description": "Perfect tenses, conditionals, and passive voice.",
  "difficulty": "intermediate",
  "position": 8,
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "1b423449-cee3-42c3-a5e0-bd0213c8bf90",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Active Voice</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A sentence where the subject performs the action of the verb.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈæktɪv vɔɪs/</div>",
      "position": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "dfd04a67-d973-4ca0-8036-a4f9f9c95d1f",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Conditional</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A sentence structure expressing a condition and its result.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/kənˈdɪʃənl/</div>",
      "position": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0d33fd47-febb-41c2-bdff-d6ede067d9b0",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">First Conditional</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes real or possible future situations: 'If' + present, will + infinitive.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/fɜːst kənˈdɪʃənl/</div>",
      "position": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "49e46d8d-0265-46ae-a236-10a15a0f1886",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Future Perfect</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes an action that will be completed before a certain time in the future: 'will have' + past participle.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈfjuːtʃə ˈpɜːfɪkt/</div>",
      "position": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "aea7dd8a-caf2-46a7-9540-3511cba8e0a9",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Mixed Conditional</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Combines different time frames in a conditional sentence.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/mɪkst kənˈdɪʃənl/</div>",
      "position": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "268fbc58-5a15-48be-8e5b-a14e403c18b0",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Passive Voice</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A sentence where the subject receives the action: 'be' + past participle.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈpæsɪv vɔɪs/</div>",
      "position": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "98cb810e-4940-4fcd-9f32-39656de0ff19",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Past Perfect</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes an action completed before another action in the past: 'had' + past participle.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/pɑːst ˈpɜːfɪkt/</div>",
      "position": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "5dc9bdd7-66d1-4bf0-b2b7-3d6cd31dde75",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Past Perfect Continuous</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Focuses on the duration of an action before another past event: 'had been' + -ing.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/pɑːst ˈpɜːfɪkt kənˈtɪnjuəs/</div>",
      "position": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "882390fa-e5c7-42d0-b60d-abc141ef62b1",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Present Perfect</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes an action with a connection to the present: 'have/has' + past participle.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈpreznt ˈpɜːfɪkt/</div>",
      "position": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "e4ffda4c-f5d8-484b-9e8b-b7d9b5011ccf",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Present Perfect Continuous</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Focuses on the duration of an action that started in the past and continues to the present: 'have/has been' + -ing.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈpreznt ˈpɜːfɪkt kənˈtɪnjuəs/</div>",
      "position": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "00e91062-a7b0-4e37-b6a5-94a2bbce23f8",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Second Conditional</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes imaginary or unlikely situations: 'If' + past simple, would + infinitive.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈsekənd kənˈdɪʃənl/</div>",
      "position": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "f96b3833-36dc-4633-85df-3509796daac0",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Third Conditional</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes unreal past situations: 'If' + past perfect, would have + past participle.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/θɜːd kənˈdɪʃənl/</div>",
      "position": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "f0fefe38-9003-406c-aab3-c462e4f7a706",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Zero Conditional</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes general truths or scientific facts: 'If' + present, present.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈzɪərəʊ kənˈdɪʃənl/</div>",
      "position": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "6733d399-fd62-4264-b9b7-ab8b06973280",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Agent</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>The person or thing performing the action in a passive sentence, often introduced by 'by'.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈeɪdʒənt/</div>",
      "position": 13
    },
    {
      "id": "af320cf1-efc4-44d4-a115-684a53907119",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Causative</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Structures used when we arrange for someone else to do something: 'have' + object + past participle.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈkɔːzətɪv/</div>",
      "position": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "43f7c2a2-80f2-4a6a-b222-c35a3f0cc6eb",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Future Continuous</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Describes an action in progress at a specific time in the future: 'will be' + -ing.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈfjuːtʃə kənˈtɪnjuəs/</div>",
      "position": 15
    },
    {
      "id": "58525b74-7727-4989-a3cd-ede61a37ae15",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Gerund</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>The -ing form of a verb functioning as a noun.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈdʒerənd/</div>",
      "position": 16
    },
    {
      "id": "36f2fb25-f65b-41aa-8385-f70f17b263b9",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Infinitive</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>The base form of a verb, often preceded by 'to'.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ɪnˈfɪnətɪv/</div>",
      "position": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "bf970489-83b4-4947-8be3-e90083043322",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Modal Verb</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Verbs such as 'can', 'should', or 'must' that express necessity, possibility, or ability.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈməʊdl vɜːb/</div>",
      "position": 18
    },
    {
      "id": "3bc98194-5720-4561-9b0a-42def0a6b261",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Participle</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Forms of a verb used to form tenses or as adjectives (present/past).</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈpɑːtɪsɪpl/</div>",
      "position": 19
    },
    {
      "id": "a654b389-8303-4887-a227-5ffcbc937b78",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Relative Clause</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A clause that adds information about a noun, usually starting with 'who', 'which', or 'that'.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈrelətɪv klɔːz/</div>",
      "position": 20
    },
    {
      "id": "4948f05a-cf7f-4899-a89b-0c46ab80b1e5",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Reported Speech</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Reporting what someone else said, often requiring backshifting verb tenses.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/rɪˈpɔːtɪd spiːtʃ/</div>",
      "position": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "7aea4492-2a6b-4d6e-bfe1-dbe45f9bd398",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Stative Verb</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Verbs describing states (e.g., 'know', 'believe') rather than actions, rarely used in continuous tenses.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈsteɪtɪv vɜːb/</div>",
      "position": 22
    },
    {
      "id": "71609da2-bf26-403d-b50d-da48559072a9",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Subject</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>The person or thing performing the action of the verb in a sentence.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈsʌbdʒɪkt/</div>",
      "position": 23
    },
    {
      "id": "e6e34422-b075-4ca7-bcc3-50a38fae98d0",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Superlative</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Form of an adjective showing the highest degree (e.g., 'the fastest').</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/suːˈpɜːlətɪv/</div>",
      "position": 24
    },
    {
      "id": "281a64aa-f22b-4fa7-88bb-2283584314d3",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Tag Question</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A short question added to the end of a statement (e.g., 'isn't it?').</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/tæɡ ˈkwestʃən/</div>",
      "position": 25
    },
    {
      "id": "c4ea56e1-8088-4d4b-868b-68b63201686e",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Tense</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>The form of a verb that indicates the time of an action.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/tens/</div>",
      "position": 26
    },
    {
      "id": "54f2d57c-402d-499f-8a20-29c0c5f9acc1",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Transitive Verb</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A verb that requires a direct object to complete its meaning.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈtrænzətɪv vɜːb/</div>",
      "position": 27
    },
    {
      "id": "6dbc6d0d-78f2-45be-9f7e-321d4b248de2",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Verb Phrase</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A combination of a main verb and its auxiliaries.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/vɜːb freɪz/</div>",
      "position": 28
    },
    {
      "id": "9b439de6-44ae-4cee-a08e-35c80097e16f",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Voice</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>The quality of a verb that indicates whether the subject performs or receives the action.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/vɔɪs/</div>",
      "position": 29
    },
    {
      "id": "7486f72e-01fd-4575-9bd0-2ed6542719c7",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Auxiliary Verb</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Verbs like 'be', 'do', or 'have' used to form tenses, moods, or voices.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ɔːɡˈzɪliəri vɜːb/</div>",
      "position": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "ddbaf267-5e52-439d-8cf0-60a3d33859ee",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Comparative</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Form of an adjective showing a higher degree (e.g., 'faster').</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/kəmˈpærətɪv/</div>",
      "position": 31
    },
    {
      "id": "7fe5bd03-d80a-41b7-8b41-838debbd26ef",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Conjunction</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A word used to connect clauses or sentences (e.g., 'and', 'but', 'although').</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/kənˈdʒʌŋkʃn/</div>",
      "position": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "f6df696a-c6a6-4d04-ab8d-814a8bf3cf92",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Determiner</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A word placed before a noun to specify quantity or possession (e.g., 'the', 'some', 'my').</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/dɪˈtɜːmɪnə(r)/</div>",
      "position": 33
    },
    {
      "id": "181fcca8-27db-4461-b1bf-05f79cceb726",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Intransitive Verb</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A verb that does not require a direct object.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ɪnˈtrænzɪtɪv vɜːb/</div>",
      "position": 34
    },
    {
      "id": "0aca747e-a308-4340-a770-21467ae5537c",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Irregular Verb</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A verb that does not follow standard rules for forming past tense or past participle.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ɪˈreɡjələ vɜːb/</div>",
      "position": 35
    },
    {
      "id": "52cde5bb-75b7-4cb6-9abd-ec99cf0bbc80",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Modal Perfect</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>Modal verb + 'have' + past participle (e.g., 'should have gone').</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈməʊdl ˈpɜːfɪkt/</div>",
      "position": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "aa9d4fd5-4bed-4288-b72e-234509fa2ad3",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Noun Phrase</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A word or group of words that functions as a noun.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/naʊn freɪz/</div>",
      "position": 37
    },
    {
      "id": "9889a62d-56c1-4a73-8b75-7b19067ea869",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Object</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>The person or thing affected by the action of a transitive verb.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈɒbdʒɪkt/</div>",
      "position": 38
    },
    {
      "id": "ea2f598b-d477-4e0e-8296-b505bfe66cef",
      "front": "<div class=\"text-6xl font-bold text-center\">Phrasal Verb</div>",
      "back": "<div class=\"text-4xl text-center\"><span class=\"text-muted-foreground text-lg block\">Meaning</span>A verb combined with an adverb or preposition to form a new meaning.</div><div class=\"text-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground mt-2\">/ˈfreɪzl vɜːb/</div>",
      "position": 39
    }
  ]
